<h1>Design and Manufacturing of an Ergonomic Lightweight Racing Seat for a Single-Seat Racing Car</h1>

<h2>Description</h2>

This project focused on the design and manufacturing of an ergonomic lightweight racing seat for a Formula-style single-seat racing car. The objective was to enhance driver comfort, safety, structural integrity, and weight reduction while ensuring manufacturability and cost efficiency.

<br />

<h2>Project Objectives</h2>

- Improve driver ergonomics and comfort
- Reduce overall seat weight
- Ensure structural stability and safety
- Select suitable lightweight materials
- Design a manufacturable racing seat
- Evaluate seat performance

<h2>Process</h2>

- Gathered driver anthropometric measurements
- Developed design concepts
- Created CAD models
- Optimized geometry for weight reduction
- Selected suitable materials
- Manufactured and assembled the seat
- Conducted testing and evaluation

